# Kubernetes Manifest Conventions

## File Organization

- Group related resources in the same directory (e.g., `01-install/`, `02-gateway/`)
- Use numbered prefixes for ordering when application order matters
- One resource per file unless tightly coupled (e.g., Service + Deployment)
- Name files after the resource: `gateway.yaml`, `httproute.yaml`, `ratelimitpolicy.yaml`

## YAML Style

- Use 2-space indentation
- Include `apiVersion`, `kind`, `metadata`, `spec` in that order
- Always set `metadata.namespace` explicitly (don't rely on context)
- Add minimal comments only where the "why" isn't obvious
- No trailing whitespace

## Labels

- Always include `app.kubernetes.io/name` and `app.kubernetes.io/part-of: connectivity-link-tutorial`
- Do not remove `kuadrant.io/*` labels — Connectivity Link requires them

## Tutorial Clarity

- Keep manifests minimal — omit optional fields that don't add tutorial value
- When showing `oc apply` commands, show the file-based approach: `oc apply -f <file>`
- Provide verification commands after each apply step
